					<br>
					
				</td>
				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<div></div><div></div><div> </div><div>The purpose of this thread is to document the expected breakpoint where a player is at the maximum potential for making GM armor based on tradeskill success equations and the imperical testing.  A few assumptions have been made and should be considered when using these numbers:</div><ul><li>The tradeskill equations were documented and provided by Tanker at a previous EQ trade fair.</li><li>Subsequently, a tradeskill calculator was developed and provided as part of the EQtraders Website.</li><li>The tradeskill equations and calculator are considered to be correct, as the calculator was used to find the breakpoints.</li><li>We know that EQ developers have the ability to designate minimum failure rates for any combine they choose.  They have asserted that GM armor in fact have minimum failure rates.  It is up to us as players to determine the specific failure rate of armor.</li><li>The following thread <a target="_blank" href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&message.id=9287">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9287</a> makes a hypothesis, based on imperical data as to the specific failure rates.  The breakpoints found here are based on those assumptions  They assume that:</li><ul><li>BP and legs have a guaranteed failure rate of 40% or a maximum success rate of 60%</li><li>Sleeves have a guaranteed failure rate of 30% or a maximum success rate of 70%</li><li>Boots, helms, and gloves have a guaranteed failure rate of 20% or a maximum success rate of 80%</li><li>Wrists have a guaranteed failure rate of 10% or a maximum success rate of 90%</li></ul></ul><p>Now that we got through all the caveots, I'll discuss the tables.  Values are calculated for 5%, 10%, and 15% tradeskill bonus items.  I did not calculate the values for 0% tradeskill bonus, since 5% items are widely available and anyone seriously making GM armor should have at least that available to them.  The tables document breakpoints for no mastery through mastery 3.  The number in the table represents the minimum skill you will need to meet or exceed the maximum success rate to make the armor.</p><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div><font face="Courier New"><strong>5%                 No M     M1     M2     M3</strong> </font></div><div><font face="Courier New">BP,Legs             284    280    272    246</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Sleeves             281    279    271    253</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Boots,Helm,Gloves   266    264    260    247</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Wrists              263    262    260    254</font></div><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div><font face="Courier New"><strong>10%                No M     M1     M2     M3</strong> </font></div><div><font face="Courier New">BP,Legs             271    268    260    235</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Sleeves             269    266    260    241</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Boots,Helm,Gloves   254    252    249    236</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Wrists              251    250    249    242</font></div><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div><font face="Courier New"><strong>15%                No M     M1     M2     M3</strong> </font></div><div><font face="Courier New">BP,Legs             250    246    248    225</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Sleeves             257    254    248    231</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Boots,Helm,Gloves   243    241    238    226</font></div><div><font face="Courier New">Wrists              240    240    238    232</font></div><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div><font face="Courier New"></font> </div><div>Reading the table:  The examples I'll provide will be on the 5% table, since most people will most likely be using that table. </div><ul><li>Assuming you have no mastery, then 284 raw skill will give you the ability to make Legs 60% of the time.  Anything above this skill will not increase your success rate. </li><li>Assuming you have 3 mastery, then 247 raw skill will give you the ability to make Boots 80% of the time.  Anything above this skill will not increase your success rate.   </li></ul><p> </p><p>I hope you find these tables informative and useful.</p><p> </p><p>Message Edited by LeanaSoulwarden on <span class="date_text">01-16-2006</span><span class="time_text">01:56 PM</span></p>
				
